{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot15EditorInspectorC","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"EditorInspector","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Class","symbolKind":"class","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"EditorInspector"}],"role":"symbol","title":"EditorInspector"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"topicSections":[{"title":"Classes","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/Signal1","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/Signal2","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/Signal3","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/Signal4","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/Signal5","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/Signal6","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/Signal7"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/editedObjectChanged","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/objectIdSelected","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/propertyDeleted","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/propertyEdited","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/propertyKeyed","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/propertySelected","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/propertyToggled","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/resourceSelected","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/restartRequested"],"title":"Instance Properties"},{"title":"Instance Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/getEditedObject()","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/getSelectedPath()"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/godotClassName"],"title":"Type Properties"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/editorinspector"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ScrollContainer"],"kind":"relationships"},{"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GodotObject","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s23CustomStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SQ","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SH","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s12IdentifiableP","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantRepresentable","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantStorable"],"type":"conformsTo"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A control used to edit properties of an object."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"EditorInspector"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the control that implements property editing in the editor’s Settings dialogs, the Inspector dock, etc. To get the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector"},{"text":" used in the editor’s Inspector dock, use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInterface\/getInspector()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" will show properties in the same order as the array returned by "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Object\/getPropertyList()","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a property’s name is path-like (i.e. if it contains forward slashes), "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector"},{"type":"text","text":" will create nested sections for “directories” along the path. For example, if a property is named "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"highlighting\/gdscript\/node_path_color"},{"type":"text","text":", it will be shown as “Node Path Color” inside the “GDScript” section nested inside the “Highlighting” section."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a property has "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PropertyUsageFlags\/propertyUsageGroup"},{"type":"text","text":" usage, it will group subsequent properties whose name starts with the property’s hint string. The group ends when a property does not start with that hint string or when a new group starts. An empty group name effectively ends the current group. "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" will create a top-level section for each group. For example, if a property with group usage is named "},{"code":"Collide With","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and its hint string is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"collide_with_"},{"type":"text","text":", a subsequent "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"collide_with_area"},{"type":"text","text":" property will be shown as “Area” inside the “Collide With” section. There is also a special case: when the hint string contains the name of a property, that property is grouped too. This is mainly to help grouping properties like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"font"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"font_color","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"font_size","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (using the hint string ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"font_"},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a property has "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PropertyUsageFlags\/propertyUsageSubgroup"},{"type":"text","text":" usage, a subgroup will be created in the same way as a group, and a second-level section will be created for each subgroup."}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlike sections created from path-like property names, "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" won’t capitalize the name for sections created from groups. So properties with group usage usually use capitalized names instead of snake_cased names."}]}],"name":"Note","type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This object emits the following signals:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/propertySelected","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/propertyKeyed"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/propertyDeleted","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/EditorInspector\/resourceSelected","isActive":true,"